result.execSummary:
The defendant Terri Lynn Johannsen was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Terri Lynn Johannsen is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Terri Lynn Johannsen was found guilty of Possess w/ Intent/Deliver Prescriptions [Modifiers: Second and Subsequent Offense, Penalties for Felonies-Class "H" Felony], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 450.11(7)(g).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: Lundell, RPR: Val Deiss, Clerk: Webb, ADA: Matthew L. Hartung, DF ATTY: John A. Kucinski, DF: Terri Lynn Johannsen appeared.  Court called at 10:29 a.m.  There is an agreement.  DE files a Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights Form.  Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights.  Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea.  Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads No Contest to Ct 1  in 14CF291 with second and subsequent offense stricken.  Court uses preliminary hearing testimony  for factual basis.  Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE adjudicated guilty of Ct 1 with second and subsequent offense stricken in 14CF291. On motion of the State, Crt dismisses Counts 2, 3 & 4. Sentencing arguments. Crt orders:

W/S 2 years probation with conditions
- DE sentenced to 6 months in the St. Croix County Jail that is Imposed and Stayed and to be used if revoked
- Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times while this case is ongoing. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.
- AODA and follow through with any recommended therapy and treatment
- DE ordered to Drug Court and to successfully complete
- 40 hours of community service 
- Court costs of $268.00 apply money on file and return balance to payor
- DE to report to probation today 09/21/15
- Bail is continued until DE signs up for probation and then it is vacated 
- 20 days to appeal
